        {
          "username": "johara mapie",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "115700326877857745375",
          "user_review_count": 1,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIGttNXOh3QKUXGj6EehdQNiWAGcoWk4D6Q-TXB9sTmwxkkJ0Rc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "I usually don\u2019t leave reviews but I had the worst experience today at this hospital. 2 of my children were born at Morgan Stanley Children Hospital and I had the best experience especially with my last born and I\u2019ve always had somewhat good experiences in the ER but today was just not it. I took my 19 year old son there for knee pain and everything went smoothly with registration and vitals. Then we got called by a nurse together with a Jewish family who came in after us. The nurse asked me and my son to sit in a hallway just a few feet away from the main entrance and took the Jewish family to a room. We sat there for almost 2 hours and no one even came to us until I got up and went to the reception and had to wait for the receptionist to appear and told her we we had been sitting in a corner for hours like chopped livers. Bear in mind that all this time we were sitting in a corner, there were new people coming in and being assigned to rooms, just not my son and he was in pain and the chairs were uncomfortable. Someone finally came to see my son about an hour after my first complaint, asked my son some questions and then told us they will send a ultrasound technician. 1 more hour passed and nothing. I go complain again to another receptionist and asked her why they couldn\u2019t at least give my son a room for him to rest his  knee. She apologizes and said she will try to do it. 15 minutes later another family comes in and gets a room and we\u2019re still waiting. After waiting another half hour, I asked my son if he\u2019d like to try another hospital, he agreed and we left and this was at around 2am. Safe to say that I will think twice before taking any of my children to this place again. I\u2019m black and Muslim and wonder if the nurse that called us in initially has any biases against us because I just can\u2019t wrap my head around what happened today. How you can just leave us in a hallway for hours and give everyone else rooms?",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNyMnM3anF3RRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x777ede51c64e1d8f!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgICr2s7jqwE%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "a year ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2024-07-06T07:08:11+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Alaina Reynolds",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "113783027465865392125",
          "user_review_count": 7,
          "user_photo_count": 1,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIqTbQRpLWkbXmZs5bkgyEqm4PFY3KWDb8o3Q0pX-2NysA2jw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "Brought my 5 month old here 12/30/23 when she caught the flu and they took such great care of us. We got there around 6:30am and were back home by 12noon. They got her a room within 15 minutes and it was our first visit (so registration & triage were included in the 15 minutes). Several doctors came in to check on her and took her situation very serious. They even gave my husband and me some breakfast. They were super kind and attentive to our precious baby girl and reassured us that she would be okay. I personally liked the culture & diversity of the staff, as well as the way they communicated with each other, my husband and I didn\u2019t have to explain her symptoms to different doctors over & over again like most hospitals, they actually took notes and communicated with each other before sending in a different doctor.  Security guards in the front were not the best, and finding park was absolutely horrible, but our experience at the hospital made it up for it which is surprising being that we were there long enough for a shift change and a whole new crew of doctors & nurses coming in. They were already privy from the notes left by the earlier crew and asked questions that showed they cared and payed attention. This children\u2019s emergency department has a very supportive overnight & morning team! We are so grateful. Happy Holidays & thank you!",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUMxbnI3V2lnRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x777ede51c64e1d8f!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgIC1nr7WigE%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "2 years ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2023-12-30T11:40:00+00:00"
        },
        {
